videos.description: Washington State's offense is powerful enough, but with Kaleb Fossum returning kicks even special teams gets in on the action as he takes the punt back 75 yards to put the Cougars up early.
videos.headline: Fossum takes punt return 75 yards to the house

videos.description: Luke Falk pass intercepted by Khari Vanderbilt and returned 20 yds to the Cal 32
videos.headline: Cal interception halts WSU drive

videos.description: River Cracraft scores his second touchdown of the game on a five-yard pass from Luke Falk to put Washington State up 28-7 on Cal heading into halftime.
videos.headline: Washington State strikes again just before halftime
WSU head coach Mike Leach wants his team to keep fighting in 2nd half

videos.description: River Cracraft makes it three touchdowns by making the leaping catch and getting the toe down to boost Washington State's lead to 35-7.
videos.headline: Cracraft's third TD catch is a thing of beauty

videos.headline: Cougars score again with TD run

videos.description: Gabe Marks sets the new Pac-12 career record for receptions when he hauls in a seven-yard touchdown catch to continue Washington State's romp over Cal.
